<subSubSection id="C32272D2FFFEFFA2F6AAF9673920FE22" pageId="4" pageNumber="257" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B872159FFFEFFA2F6AAF9673920FE22" blockId="4.[144,759,1789,1903]" lastBlockId="4.[806,1421,397,450]" pageId="4" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="B94CFD4BFFFEFFA2F6AAF9673D5FF8F3" box="[144,262,1790,1811]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="257">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body moderately high with postero-dorsal angle ill defined or completely absent, head capsule of ‘chydorid-type’ (strongly compressed dorso-ventrally), head shield with acute rostrum, valves without marginal setae, antenna II relatively long, mandible attached to point of joint of head shield and valve.
</paragraph>
